The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, June 30: State-run Steel Authority of India Ltd (SAIL) has joined hands with the Shipping Corporation of India to promote a joint venture company, which would provide SAIL with shipping related services for importing coking coal. The venture may also participate in worldwide dry bulk shipping trade and can have other companies as partners, a SAIL statement said.                            
	 Calcutta, June 30: Usha Martin Ltd and BHP Billiton have signed an agreement to set up a joint venture companyBharat Minex Pvt Ltd to explore minerals in Jharkhand.                             
	 New Delhi, June 30: The Supreme Court today stayed the Andhra Pradesh High Courts order allowing some companies to export non-basmati rice which is banned by the Centre.                                                                                                                         
